title: '[220 f $ [t/3: cont1 more 2] 1.5 _]'
pid: 49ae48ed-6c5b-4956-8a33-c87d5354ba07
body: |2-
  says the same thing.
  The "1 cont 2" is 3 events,
  the first two (cont1 more) being the continuous movement
  over 2/3 of the inner-bracketed time
  from the 1 to the 2, where it lands and stays for the rest of the loop.
